AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.sixty (60) illegal aliens: aliens found in the tractor trailer during a secondary inspection at the United States Border Patrol check point, loaded at Diesel Impact 2000 off of Highway 359, claimed to be going to McAllen or San Antonio but were actually headed elsewhere, evidence presented in preliminary examination hearings, sixty aliens were found in the rear of the trailer, fifty-nine aliens present at the United States Border Patrol check point and one alien in the hospital due to taking an improper medication
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Yusif Ahmed Rufied: individual from Ghana, Africa, living in Quebec, Montreal, Canada, claimed to be a driver in training, slept in the tractor trailer from Midnight to 6:00 a.m., was awake when they went to Diesel Impact 2000, found with $1700, charged by criminal complaint on May 26, 2006, held by the United States District Court for the Southern District of Texas, identified as the individual in the United States District Court for the Southern District of Texas wearing an orange jumpsuit
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Martin Adaboh: individual from Ghana, Africa, living in Quebec, Montreal, Canada, codefendant, requested an attorney during questioning, met a woman named Claudia at the Monterrey Inn, involved in smuggling aliens, claimed they were going to San Antonio, received $1000 from Martin Adaboh
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.United States District Court for the Sou: court that found probable cause to hold Yusif Ahmed Rufied and held a preliminary examination hearing on June 2, 2006, issued a document on June 7, 2006
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Adriana Arce Flores: United States official who signed the document on June 7, 2006
